  "text": ", which amounts to the standard KL retrieval approach [CITATION_1] ; this document-query similarity measure is used in our methods when employed over the LM initial ranking. The second method, denoted MRF, is the Markov Random Field approach [CITATION_2] employed with the sequential dependence model (SDM), which is a state-ofthe-art content-based retrieval approach [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Our methods use sim(q, d) def = p(d, q), which is induced using SDM, when operating on the MRF initial ranking. The free parameters of SDM, λT , λO and λU are set to 0.85, 0.1, and 0.05, respectively, as these values are known to yield effective performance [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . For the experiments with MRF, the document language model smoothing parameter, μ, was set to 2500 following previous recommendations [CITATION_7] .",
